-- French president to meet Siemens, Mitsubishi heads on Tuesday
-- By James Regan
-- Mon Jun 16, 2014 10:26AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, June 16 (Reuters) - French President Francois Hollande will meet with the heads of Germany's Siemens <SIEGn.DE> and Japan's Mitsubishi Heavy Industries (MHI) <7011.T> on Tuesday morning, the president's office said in a statement on Monday.

The meeting with Joe Kaeser and Shunichi Miyanaga is due to take place at 0825 GMT, according to the statement.